        <!-- Main Article Content -->
        <section class="article-content">
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              <span class="article-para-word-cap">L</span>et’s be real. HSC
              admission season in Bangladesh feels like a mix of panic,
              pressure, and your aunt asking “Kon college e porbi?” for the
              tenth time. It’s confusing, weirdly intense, and unless you’ve got
              a cousin who just went through it, no one seems to explain it
              properly.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              So here’s a clear, honest, and straight-to-the-point guide that
              helps. Whether you’re aiming for Rajuk, Viqarunnisa, or Dhaka
              College, or just want to get into a solid college and start fresh,
              this is for you.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="article-heading--h2" id="step1">
            Step 1: Know What You’re Applying For
          </h2>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              Before anything else, figure out what you need to get in. Most
              colleges (especially top ones) want:
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list">
            <li>GPA 5.00 if you’re applying to science</li>
            <li>A decent GPA (4.5+ usually safe) for commerce or humanities</li>
            <li>
              Some ask for subject-specific grades especially in math or science
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">You’ll need:</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list">
            <li>SSC transcript and certificate</li>
            <li>Birth certificate</li>
            <li>Recent passport-sized photos</li>
            <li>Mobile number used during SSC registration</li>
            <li>Guardian’s NID (sometimes asked during verification)</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Scan everything. Keep it in your phone
              and Google Drive. Losing the original the night before the
              deadline = pain.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="article-heading--h2" id="step2">
            Step 2: Decide Which Colleges to Aim For
          </h2>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              There are two types of colleges when it comes to admission:
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list">
            <li>
              Merit-based colleges via the government portal - like Rajuk,
              Viqarunnisa, Dhaka College, Holy Cross, Ideal, etc.
            </li>
            <li>
              Institutions like
              <a href="https://ndc.edu.bd/" class="article-link">Notre Dame</a>
              &
              <a href="http://www.hcc.edu.bd/" class="article-link"
                >Holy Cross</a
              >
              - they run separate admission processes with their own forms &
              tests.
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              So don’t put Notre Dame in your government preference list - it
              won’t work. If you’re applying to these colleges, check their
              websites or Facebook pages directly.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              For the government portal, you’ll list up to 10 choices - rank
              them smartly:
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list">
            <li>2–3 dream colleges</li>
            <li>4–5 mid-tier options</li>
            <li>2–3 backups (realistic safety net)</li>
          </ul>

          <h2 class="article-heading--h2" id="step3">
            Step 3: Make a Study Plan
          </h2>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              Look, you don’t need a bullet journal or 4-color highlighters.
              Just write down:
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list">
            <li>What subjects you're struggling with</li>
            <li>Topics you want to revise before college starts</li>
            <li>
              Entrance prep (if you're applying to Notre Dame, Holy Cross, etc.)
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              If you’re still in “post-SSC chill mode,” that’s fine. But HSC
              isn’t slow-paced. Having a headstart makes life easier later.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="article-heading--h2" id="step4">
            Step 4: Online Form? Here’s What Actually Matters
          </h2>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              If you’re going through
              <a
                href="https://xiclassadmissiongovbd.com/apply-online/"
                target="_blank"
                class="article-link"
                >xiclassadmission.gov.bd</a
              >, here’s how it works:
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list article-list--ordered">
            <li>Choose up to 10 colleges</li>
            <li>Rank them carefully</li>
            <li>Submit with a small fee via bKash/Nagad</li>
            <li>Wait for your result (they’ll notify you via SMS)</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">Things to keep in mind:</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list">
            <li>
              Choose shift wisely (morning/evening) - some colleges have
              separate merit lists
            </li>
            <li>Save your transaction ID</li>
            <li>
              Don’t panic if you don’t get your top choice - there are multiple
              phases for migration and re-application
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              🎯 <strong>Again:</strong> Notre Dame, Holy Cross, etc. do not use
              this process. You need to collect and submit their form
              separately.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="article-heading--h2" id="step5">
            Step 5: Prep for Mini Admission Tests (If Needed)
          </h2>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              Colleges like Notre Dame, Holy Cross, and a few others might ask
              for small written tests, usually based on SSC-level English and
              general knowledge.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">So brush up on:</p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list">
            <li>Review the basics of all relevant subjects from SSC</li>
            <li>Current events and GK</li>
            <li>Solving physics and math questions faster</li>
          </ul>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              If you’ve taken board exams, you’re more than ready. You just need
              to dust off the brain cells and review a little.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="article-heading--h2" id="step6">
            Step 6: Plan for Fees (Yeah, It Adds Up Fast)
          </h2>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              HSC admission isn’t super expensive, but the little things add up:
            </p>
          </div>
          <ul class="article-list">
            <li>Online form fee (around ৳150–200)</li>
            <li>
              College admission fees (can be ৳2,000–৳12,000 depending on
              institution)
            </li>
            <li>
              Uniforms, books, ID photos, coaching fees if you plan to join any
            </li>
          </ul>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              Start tracking early so nothing catches you off guard.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="article-heading--h2" id="step7">Step 7: Ask for Help</h2>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              If this whole process is making you overthink everything, talk to
              someone. Ask a friend, older cousin, or a teacher. Even the local
              photocopy guy near the college usually knows what’s up.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              This isn’t about being the smartest in the room - it’s about
              getting through the process without messing up something small.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h2 class="article-heading--h2" id="bonus">
            Bonus: This Is Your Fresh Start (Rebrand Time)
          </h2>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              HSC life gives you a rare chance to change how you show up. If you
              want to switch from the “I barely passed SSC” kid to the “I’m
              actually trying now” version of yourself - this is it.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              New college, new habits, maybe even a new group of friends.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              So start fresh. Get organized. Write that first list. You don’t
              need to have everything figured out, but knowing where you’re
              headed makes a big difference.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              If this helped, keep an eye out as we’ll be dropping more guides
              to help with HSC life, university prep, and figuring out what
              comes next.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="article-para">
            <p class="article-para-text">
              And yeah, if your relatives ask again “kothay apply korcho?” - now
              you’ve got answers.
            </p>
          </div>
